    slug: "marital-discord-causes-and-cures",
    description: `Marital Discord - Causes and Cures is a practical and comprehensive Islamic book in English that addresses the widespread problem of conflict and disharmony within Muslim marriages, offering both a thorough analysis of the root causes of marital problems and a detailed set of Islamic solutions and remedies drawn from the Quran, the authentic Sunnah, and the accumulated wisdom of Islamic scholarship. The book recognises that marital discord is a universal human challenge that affects Muslim families just as it affects families of all backgrounds, and it approaches this sensitive topic with the compassion, seriousness, and practical focus that it deserves. The author begins by establishing the Islamic framework for understanding marriage, explaining that Islam views the marital relationship as a sacred covenant (mithaq ghaliz) between a man and a woman, based on mutual love, mercy (mawaddah wa rahmah), and shared responsibility. This foundational understanding shapes the entire approach of the book, as every cause of discord and every proposed cure is evaluated against the standard that Islam sets for a healthy and righteous marriage. The book identifies and analyses the major causes of marital discord in detail, covering communication breakdown, financial stress, interference from in-laws and extended family, differences in expectations and priorities, intimacy issues, unmet emotional needs, cultural conflicts, personality clashes, and the failure to fulfil Islamic marital rights and responsibilities. For each cause, the author provides both a clear explanation of why it leads to conflict and practical Islamic guidance on how to address it, drawing upon relevant Quranic verses, hadith narrations, and the rulings of Islamic jurisprudence. The cures section of the book offers a structured programme for resolving marital conflicts, including guidance on effective Islamic communication, the importance of patience and forbearance (hilm), the role of mutual respect and kindness, the Islamic method of dispute resolution involving family mediators, the concept of giving gifts to foster affection, and the ultimate recourse to Islamic counselling and, if necessary, arbitration (tahkim) as prescribed in the Quran. The book also addresses special situations such as domestic abuse, addiction, and situations where reconciliation is not possible, providing clear guidance on the Islamic rulings that apply in these difficult circumstances. The author writes in clear and accessible English, making the book suitable for a wide readership including married couples, those preparing for marriage, Islamic counsellors, and community leaders who assist families in distress.`,
    metaDescription: "Marital Discord - Causes and Cures provides Islamic solutions for marriage problems using Quran, Sunnah, and scholarly wisdom for conflict resolution."
