    slug: "masajid-ka-bayan",
    description: `Masajid Ka Bayan is a comprehensive Urdu-language Islamic book that provides a detailed exposition of the status, virtues, rulings, and etiquettes of mosques (masajid) in Islam, offering readers a thorough understanding of one of the most central institutions of Muslim religious and community life. The book establishes from the outset the supreme importance of mosques in Islam by presenting the relevant Quranic verses and hadith narrations that describe mosques as the most beloved of places to Allah, the houses of worship that were established on the foundation of taqwa from the very first day, and the centres around which the spiritual, educational, and social life of the Muslim community revolves. The author covers the historical development of mosques from the time of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), beginning with the Prophet's Mosque in Madinah and the Quba Mosque, through the great mosques of the early caliphates and the architectural masterpieces of subsequent Islamic civilisations, to the mosques of the contemporary Muslim world. The book discusses the essential components and features of a mosque according to Islamic tradition, including the prayer hall (musalla), the minbar (pulpit), the mihrab (prayer niche), the minaret, and the ablution area, explaining the significance and function of each element. The rulings section of the book provides detailed guidance on the Islamic jurisprudence related to mosques, covering topics such as the construction and maintenance of mosques, the conditions for valid prayer in a mosque, the etiquettes of entering and leaving the mosque, the virtue of praying in congregation, the rules regarding the Imam and the muazzin, the permissibility and prohibition of various activities within the mosque, the rights of the mosque over the community, and the ruling on mosques that have been abandoned or neglected. The author also addresses the role of mosques beyond the five daily prayers, discussing their function as centres of education (the tradition of halaqah and dars), community gathering and social welfare, conflict resolution, and the dissemination of Islamic knowledge. A dedicated section covers the etiquettes that every Muslim should observe when visiting the mosque, including cleanliness, modest dress, lowering the voice, avoiding worldly talk, and maintaining the sanctity of the space. The book also discusses contemporary issues related to mosques, such as the management of mosque committees, the role of women in mosques, the use of technology in mosque administration, and the challenges facing mosques in non-Muslim majority countries. Written in scholarly yet accessible Urdu, Masajid Ka Bayan is an essential reference for mosque committees, imams, students of Islamic knowledge, and every Muslim who wishes to understand and uphold the honour of the house of Allah.`,
    metaDescription: "Masajid Ka Bayan offers a comprehensive Urdu guide on mosque virtues, rulings, history, and the central role of masjids in Muslim community life."
